quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  59,17,The end of both will be that they will be tossed in hell and remain there forever. Thus shall be the reward of the wrongdoers
  59,18,"O believers! Fear Allah and let every soul see what it is sending for the morrow (Hereafter). Fear Allah, surely Allah is aware of all your actions"
  59,19,"Be not like those who forgot Allah, as a result Allah caused them to forget themselves, it is they who are the transgressors"
  59,20,"The companions of hell and the companions of paradise are not equals, of course the companions of paradise are far superior"
  59,21,"If We had sent down this Qurâ€™an on a mountain, you would have seen it humble itself and split asunder from the fear of Allah, We are citing this example for mankind, so that they may take heed"
  59,22,"Allah is He, besides Whom there is no god, the Knower of the unseen and the seen. He is the Compassionate, the Merciful"
  59,23,"Allah is He, besides Whom there is no god, the King, the Holy, the Giver of peace, the Granter of security, the Guardian, the Almighty, the Irresistible, the Supreme: Glory be to Allah! He is far above the shirk they commit (by associating other gods with Him)"
  59,24,"He is Allah, the Creator, the Evolver, the Modeler. His are the most beautiful names. All that is in the heavens and the earth declares His glory, and He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"